snippet.textDisplay:
Hope we get some international aid for a change!
And if not, we should keep our money to spend at home. Personally I think we should spend our own money at home for the next two years, no holidays to Spain so they can go back to a goat herding country, don't buy any cars from Germany if they don't want to give us a free trade deal, let the French keep their wine, not sure what Lithuania brought to the EU table or Greece with their non payment of taxes. We need a Australia system in the UK so we only let in skilled workers not the benefit freeloaders, and unskilled labour between the ages of 21 to 35.
